==Presence outside Earth== It is generally thought that the presence of carbonates in [[Rock (geology)|rock]] is strong evidence for the presence of liquid water. Recent observations of the [[planetary nebula]] [[NGC 6302]] show evidence for carbonates in space,<ref>Kemper, F., Molster, F.J., Jager, C. and Waters, L.B.F.M. (2001) The mineral composition and spatial distribution of the dust ejecta of NGC 6302. ''Astronomy & Astrophysics'' '''394''', 679–690.</ref> where aqueous alteration similar to that on Earth is unlikely. Other minerals have been proposed which would fit the observations.
